The paper proposes a framework for robust subspace clustering, which involves learning a linear transformation on subspaces using matrix rank as the optimization criteria. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses online learning and dimensionality reduction, which are topics that fall under the information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories, respectively.
